# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STRICT WHITELIST .gitignore
# Track ONLY the public-facing code distributed to users (the npm package).
# Everything else — specs, plans, reports, dev-tooling, .github, tests,
# .claude, node_modules — is ignored. The allow-list below mirrors the
# package.json "files" field (the authoritative distribution whitelist).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1. Ignore everything by default…
*

# 2. …but still descend into directories so the allow-list can reach files.
!*/

# 3. Allow-list: repo-public root files.
!/.gitignore
!/package.json
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/CONTRIBUTING.md

# 4. Allow-list: distributed code trees (== package.json "files").
!/bin/**
!/src/**
!/hooks/**
!/rules/**
!/skills/**
# Native Rust scanner crate — source of a runtime binary. Build artifacts
# (target/) are re-ignored by tools/leakscan/.gitignore. Whole-crate tracking.
!/tools/**

# 5. Re-ignore the non-distributed bits inside those trees
#    (mirrors the "!…" negations in package.json "files").
*.test.mjs
rules/baseline/fixtures/
rules/baseline/selftest.config.mjs
.worktrees/

# scratch / demo workspaces
tmp/
